Omit

Omit: Pick<T, Exclude<keyof T, K>>
  • Defined in utils/Typescript.ts:24

Omit certains keys from an object type.

Example:

interface Test {
 a: string;
 b: number;
 c: boolean;
}

Omit a single property:

type OmitA = Omit<Test, "a">; // Equivalent to: {b: number, c: boolean}

Or, to omit multiple properties:

type OmitAB = Omit<Test, "a"|"b">; // Equivalent to: {c: boolean}

Static Optional contextType

contextType: Context<any>

Inherited from Component.contextType

  • Defined in /Users/artalat/Coding/bluebase/core/node_modules/@types/react/index.d.ts:377

If set, this.context will be set at runtime to the current value of the given Context.

Usage:

type MyContext = number
const Ctx = React.createContext<MyContext>(0)

class Foo extends React.Component {
  static contextType = Ctx
  context!: React.ContextType<typeof Ctx>
  render () {
    return <>My context's value: {this.context}</>;
  }
}
see

https://reactjs.org/docs/context.html#classcontexttype

Const applyStyles

  • applyStyles(name: string, Component: ComponentWithDefaultStyles, stylesParam: MaybeThunk<ComponentStyles>): React.ComponentType<any>
    • Defined in themes/helpers/applyStyles.tsx:33

    Merges component styles from different sources and passes on the the component as 'styles' prop.

    Following sources are considered as style sources. (In order of least important first):

    1. defaultStyles: A component may provide default styles as a "defaultStyles" static property of component. This is similar to defaultProps in react.
    2. stylesParam: 3rd property of this function. Note: Component Registry passes 'styles' prop from it's registry item.
    3. Themes: From theme.components[componentName] property of current theme.
    4. styles prop: The styles prop passed on to the component during usage.
